title: Sublime - Self Titled Vinyl rip @ 24bits per 96k samples/second
description:
Here is Sublime&#039;s Legendary self titled album, from the pretty pictured limited edition pressing. 

Recorded in delicious 24 bit HD audio 96 thousands times EVERY second.


Track list is as follows :

01 Garden Grove
02 What I Got
03 Wrong Way
04 Same in the End
05 Riot Song (I&#039;m Lazy)
06 Santeria
07 Seed
08 Paddle Out
09 Get Ready
10 Caress Me Down


Yes that is all 10 tracks of this specific pressing :( I was really looking forward to the other What I Got 
and summertime.

This is by no means an audiophiles cream dream, but I think it will suffice. I did this up with a tad 

more professionalism (adobe auditioned em to get the beginnings and ends just right) so I hope you 

like it. The first track has a skip. It goes like " I got the deuce deuce in the trunk of my {{ skip}}Oh yeah" 

and I tried to rerecord it 6 times but the same skip occurred every time in the same spot. But this is 

the first recording of the song I flaced for all those worried of degradation on the 2-6th recording. 

There may be more but I just listened to it all the way through once and I didn&#039;t hear any. Sorry if 

there are but there is nothing I can/could do about it.
